Calistrian Prostitute (Calistria)		KEY:Trait ~ Calistrian Prostitute	NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.ReligionTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Calistrian Prostitute],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.ReligionTrait]							DESCISPI:YES	DESC:You worked in one of Calistria's temples as a sacred prostitute, and you know how to flatter, please, and (most of all) listen. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Gather Information and Sense Motive checks.																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.15	ASPECT:SkillBonus|You gain a +1 trait bonus on Gather Information and Sense Motive checks.	BONUS:SKILL|Sense Motive|1|TYPE=Trait
Sacred Avenger (Calistria)			KEY:Trait ~ Sacred Avenger		NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.ReligionTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Sacred Avenger],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.ReligionTrait]								DESCISPI:YES	DESC:You have a special connection between you and Calistria that enhances your ability to achieve vengeance. When a creature damages you with a weapon, on your next turn you gain a +1 trait bonus on weapon damage against that creature. If this creature is your ilduliel (see page 8), this bonus increases to +2.																					SOURCEPAGE:p.15
Sovyrian Pantheist (Any Elven Deity)	KEY:Trait ~ Sovyrian Pantheist	NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.ReligionTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Sovyrian Pantheist],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.ReligionTrait]								DESCISPI:YES	DESC:Strongly influenced by the elves' mysterious other realm, you embrace obscure elven deities that have little influence on Golarion. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Knowledge (history) checks to recognize or evaluate art, Knowledge (architecture and engineering) checks, Survival checks to hunt game, Constitution checks to run, and Spellcraft checks involving crystals or gems.										SOURCEPAGE:p.15	ASPECT:SkillBonus|+1 trait bonus on Knowledge (history) checks to recognize or evaluate art, Knowledge (architecture and engineering) checks, Survival checks to hunt game, Constitution checks to run, and Spellcraft checks involving crystals or gems.
Starchild (Desna)					KEY:Trait ~ Starchild			NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.ReligionTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Starchild],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.ReligionTrait]									DESCISPI:YES	DESC:The Song of the Spheres sensed your love of travel and promised you would always be able to find your way home. You can automatically determine where true north is. You gain a +4 trait bonus on Survival checks to avoid becoming lost.																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.15	ASPECT:SkillBonus|+4 trait bonus on Survival checks to avoid becoming lost
Wasp Whisperer (Calistria)			KEY:Trait ~ Wasp Whisperer		NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.ReligionTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Wasp Whisperer],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.ReligionTrait]								DESCISPI:YES	DESC:Your association with Calistria's church has toughened your flesh against venom and blessed you with the ability to influence wasps and similar insectile vermin. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Fortitude saving throws against poison. You may make Diplomacy checks (or wild empathy checks if you are a druid or ranger) to improve a Hostile or Unfriendly insectile vermin's attitude toward Indifferent.						SOURCEPAGE:p.15	ASPECT:SaveBonus|+1 trait bonus on Fortitude saving throws against poison	ASPECT:SkillBonus|You may make Diplomacy checks (or wild empathy checks if you are a druid or ranger) to improve a Hostile or Unfriendly insectile vermin's attitude toward Indifferent.

